The article is a statement by President Barack Obama expressing condolences for the passing of Zambian President Michael Chilufya Sata. The President sends his condolences to First Lady Dr. Christine Kaseba-Sata and the people of Zambia. The United States is committed to its friendship and partnership with Zambia and supports a peaceful transition of power. The US will continue to enhance bilateral relations, support Zambia's democratic traditions, increase development, and promote a free and just society.